## Building an Image Carousel in React

**Mental model:** A carousel is an index into a slides array plus a translated track. `next`/`prev` move the index (wrapping with modulo); a CSS `translateX(-index * 100%)` slides the strip. Autoplay is an interval that calls `next`, paused on hover and cleaned up on unmount.

### Step 1 — Index + a sliding track
```jsx
const [index, setIndex] = useState(0);
<div style={{ display: 'flex', transform: `translateX(${-index * 100}%)`, transition: 'transform 0.4s' }}>
```

### Step 2 — Prev / next with wrap
```jsx
const next = () => setIndex((i) => (i + 1) % slides.length);
const prev = () => setIndex((i) => (i - 1 + slides.length) % slides.length);
```

### Step 3 — Dot indicators
Render one dot per slide; the active one is highlighted and clickable.

```jsx
{slides.map((_, i) => <button key={i} aria-current={i === index} onClick={() => setIndex(i)} />)}
```

### Step 4 — Autoplay with cleanup
```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  if (paused) return;
  const id = setInterval(next, 3000);
  return () => clearInterval(id);
}, [paused, slides.length]);
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Single slide | Hide arrows/dots. |
| Hover during autoplay | Pause via `paused` state. |
| Unmount | Effect cleanup clears the interval. |

**Interview tip:** Driving the slide purely with `transform: translateX` (GPU-composited) instead of swapping `display`/`left` is the performance detail — and remember to pause autoplay on hover and clear the interval on unmount.

